title: No.5 Bulldogs Swept by No. 9 Wildcats
text:
No.5 Bulldogs Swept by No. 9 Wildcats 
By Norman Seawright III October 17, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 11:06 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The No. 5 University of Minnesota-Duluth (UMD) volleyball team was upset by No. 9 Wayne State (WSU) in straight sets at home. 
Despite comebacks in all three sets, Monica Turner's error-free 11 kills, and four blocks for Taylor Wissbroecker, the Bulldogs were swept by the Wildcats.
